Package de.unisb.cs.st.javaslicer.common.classRepresentation

Class AbstractInstructionInstance

java.lang.Object
de.unisb.cs.st.javaslicer.common.classRepresentation.AbstractInstructionInstance
All Implemented Interfaces:
InstructionInstance, Comparable<InstructionInstance>
public class AbstractInstructionInstance
extends Object
implements InstructionInstance
Standard implementation of an InstructionInstance. Consists of the wrapped AbstractInstruction, an occurence number, the stack depth, the absolute instance number, the instance type and additonal information provided depending on the type.
Author:
Clemens Hammacher

      public long getOccurrenceNumber()

      Returns the occurrence number of this instance. It always counts upwards from 0 on, so the numbering is in reverse order when traversing a trace backwards.

    • getAdditionalInfo

      public InstructionInstanceInfo getAdditionalInfo()
      Description copied from interface: InstructionInstance
      Returns additonal information which corresponds to this InstructionInstance. The kind of information depends of the type of the corresponding instruction (getInstruction().getType()):
      • for InstructionType.ARRAY, it's an ArrayInstruction.ArrayInstrInstanceInfo
      • for InstructionType.FIELD, it's an FieldInstruction.FieldInstrInstanceInfo
      • for InstructionType.NEWARRAY, it's an NewArrayInstruction.NewArrayInstrInstanceInfo
      • for InstructionType.MULTIANEWARRAY, it's an MultiANewArrayInstruction.MultiANewArrayInstrInstanceInfo
      • for InstructionType.TYPE, it's an TypeInstruction.TypeInstrInstanceInfo
      • for the rest, this method returns null
      Specified by:
      getAdditionalInfo in interface InstructionInstance
      Returns:
      additional information for this InstructionInstance
